Am I over-thinking or not thinking at all?

Posted by raymondlewallen on March 1, 2005

The past few days I’ve found myself asking some really dumb
questions that I know the answers to.  Not that I don’t normally
do this, but not to the extent I have been lately.  .Net
(framework, CLR, CTS, my own code, other peoples code and just the size
of it all and trying to understand it all (impossible, I know)) and the
combination of some extremely complex business logic might be to
blame.  Is my head getting too cluttered?  Have I overloaded
myself with so many diverse topics lately that I’ve become some sort of
babbling wonder spouting non-sense?  I just had an email
conversation with some friends about GC, and asked a very basic
question about GC that I’ve known the answer to for years.  I
better stop before I get further behind.  Needless to say, take my
next few posts with caution.  I think I’m nearing the mandatory
vacation time away from technology for a few days.  There’s no
telling what I might try to convince you to believe right now.

This might just be the beginning stages of minor burnout.  I better spend a little more time with my family and guitar and maybe some ET for awhile.

Currently listening to:Machine Gun – Jimi Hendrix
